  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I find Twitter statistics by country?",
  "response": "Finding Twitter statistics by country can be useful for understanding user demographics, engagement, and trends. Here are some sources and methods to access such data:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Official Twitter Resources**\n   - **Twitter Insights (via Twitter Ads):**\n     - If you have access to Twitter Ads, you can use Twitter's **Audience Insights** tool. This provides demographic data, including country-specific statistics for Twitter users.\n     - Visit: [https://ads.twitter.com](https://ads.twitter.com)\n   - **Twitter Transparency Reports:**\n     - Twitter occasionally releases transparency reports that include data on requests from governments, which can indirectly provide insights into user activity by country.\n     - Visit: [https://transparency.twitter.com](https://transparency.twitter.com)\n\n---\n\n### **2. Third-Party Analytics Tools**\n   - **Statista:**\n     - Statista often publishes Twitter statistics by country, including user numbers, usage trends, and demographics.\n     - Visit: [https://www.statista.com](https://www.statista.com)\n   - **Hootsuite:**\n     - Hootsuite\u2019s annual Digital Report often includes Twitter usage data by country.\n     - Visit: [https://www.hootsuite.com](https://www.hootsuite.com)\n   - **Social Blade:**\n     - Social Blade provides Twitter statistics and rankings by country and region.\n     - Visit: [https://socialblade.com](https://socialblade.com)\n\n---\n\n### **3. Research and Market Reports**\n   - **eMarketer:**\n     - eMarketer offers detailed reports on social media usage, including Twitter, by country.\n     - Visit: [https://www.emarketer.com](https://www.emarketer.com)\n   - **Pew Research Center:**\n     - Pew Research occasionally publishes reports on social media usage, including Twitter, with country-specific insights.\n     - Visit: [https://www.pewresearch.org](https://www.pewresearch.org)\n\n---\n\n### **4. Academic and Government Sources**\n   - Universities and research institutions often conduct studies on social media usage by country. Search for academic papers via Google Scholar or JSTOR.\n   - Government statistics agencies may also publish social media usage data.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Custom Data Requests**\n   - If you need specific data, consider reaching out to data aggregators or market research firms like **Nielsen**, **Comscore**, or **GlobalWebIndex**.\n\n---\n\nLet me know if you'd like help navigating any of these resources!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
